  "target_response": {
    "text": "This is a very doable, safe cut if you start now — roughly two kilos across eight weeks is about 0.3 kg per week. The plan: run a modest daily calorie deficit from this week, keep protein high and your strength and rowing volume in place so the loss comes from fat rather than muscle, and aim to arrive at 72 kg a full week before the weigh-in so race week needs no manipulation at all. Weigh yourself each morning and steer by the weekly average, not single days. What you're right to avoid is the acute stuff — sauna cuts, water loading, plastic layers — which is where lightweight rowing gets genuinely dangerous. Since this is a sanctioned category, loop in your club coach on the plan, and a sports dietitian is worth it if the deficit stalls or training quality drops.",
